    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer63657853" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13513412601740244807">Although a huge fan of Greg Iles, and especially enjoying the previous novels with the character of Penn Cage, had I known this book was about dogfighting I would never have bothered to pick it up. I found this book to be disturbing, disgusting and stomach churning. I had to skim over several passages because I knew if I had read them, these invoked images would have haunted me for a very long time. An avid animal lover, I just found this subject far to revolting to ever be able to consider it e</span>
  <span id="freeText13513412601740244807" style="display:none">Although a huge fan of Greg Iles, and especially enjoying the previous novels with the character of Penn Cage, had I known this book was about dogfighting I would never have bothered to pick it up. I found this book to be disturbing, disgusting and stomach churning. I had to skim over several passages because I knew if I had read them, these invoked images would have haunted me for a very long time. An avid animal lover, I just found this subject far to revolting to ever be able to consider it entertainment in any way, shape or form. The characters in the book barely had their feathers ruffled either when confronted by this disgusting "sport" and I found that to be equally disturbing. Definitely not for me. I am not sure I will ever be looking forward to a new release from Greg Iles again.</span>
