<div id="review_87433697" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/87433697" />
    <a title="John DeDakis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1807899-john-dedakis"><img alt="John DeDakis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1468269466p2/1807899.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/87433697?book_show_action=true">Jan 30, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John DeDakis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John DeDakis" href="/user/show/1807899-john-dedakis">John DeDakis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780007326358" href="/book/show/7618452-the-devil-s-punchbowl">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer87433697" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14052958874449003722">I REALLY like the way this guy writes. He grabs my attention from page one and makes me keep wanting to turn pages. His characters are believable and well textured. His settings are vivid. His plotting is intricate. Each paragraph flows logically from the previous one and the writing is straightforward, not pretentious. I&apos;ve only read a few of his books, beginning wth &quot;Turning Angel,&quot; but I want to read more because he hasn&apos;t disappointed me yet. </span>
  <span id="freeText14052958874449003722" style="display:none">I REALLY like the way this guy writes. He grabs my attention from page one and makes me keep wanting to turn pages. His characters are believable and well textured. His settings are vivid. His plotting is intricate. Each paragraph flows logically from the previous one and the writing is straightforward, not pretentious. I've only read a few of his books, beginning wth "Turning Angel," but I want to read more because he hasn't disappointed me yet. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14052958874449003722" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


