<div id="review_2350133425" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2350133425" />
    <a title="LATOYA JOVENA" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41700915-latoya-jovena"><img alt="LATOYA JOVENA" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1427896211p2/41700915.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2350133425?book_show_action=true">Apr 14, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="LATOYA JOVENA" class="user" itemprop="url" name="LATOYA JOVENA" href="/user/show/41700915-latoya-jovena">LATOYA JOVENA</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780743292511" href="/book/show/2967316-the-devil-s-punchbowl">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2350133425" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17946979906713079540">I&apos;m not crazy about the voice and the entire tale is too far fetched to be immersive. <br/>The way the women think and act make it clear the author is a male. Also he seems to like describing the brutalization of female bodies. <br/>Finally there are detailed passages of dog abuse. Greg Iles did not make a fan of me. </span>
  <span id="freeText17946979906713079540" style="display:none">I'm not crazy about the voice and the entire tale is too far fetched to be immersive. <br />The way the women think and act make it clear the author is a male. Also he seems to like describing the brutalization of female bodies. <br />Finally there are detailed passages of dog abuse. Greg Iles did not make a fan of me. </span>
