    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3486082078" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3486082078" />
    <a title="casey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68786440-casey"><img alt="casey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642275518p2/68786440.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3486082078?book_show_action=true">Aug 15, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="casey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="casey" href="/user/show/68786440-casey">casey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3486082078" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11874914713969038678">Yet another brilliant book by Greg Iles. The only author I&apos;ve read for the last month as I work my way relentlessly through his six and a half-book &apos;Penn Cage&apos; series as I also care for my 5 month old infant!<br/><br/>Iles is a new author to me, but I seem to be hooked. Let&apos;s just say I am quite attached to Penn Cage&apos;s family. Let me be clear... this book is particularly dark. More so than the first 2. We have an introduction to a corruption scheme involving the casino barges that goes beyond the gambling</span>
  <span id="freeText11874914713969038678" style="display:none">Yet another brilliant book by Greg Iles. The only author I've read for the last month as I work my way relentlessly through his six and a half-book 'Penn Cage' series as I also care for my 5 month old infant!<br /><br />Iles is a new author to me, but I seem to be hooked. Let's just say I am quite attached to Penn Cage's family. Let me be clear... this book is particularly dark. More so than the first 2. We have an introduction to a corruption scheme involving the casino barges that goes beyond the gambling of cards and roulette but involves the underworld of prostitution and dog fighting. As an animal lover it doesn't make for easy reading at times as the thought of dog-fighting is just horrendous to me. However, there is no point in pretending such things do not go on and that the people involved are cruel and ruthless to the extreme. In this book, that cruelty and ruthlessness extends beyond their animal victims to humans too.<br /><br />Iles is a gifted writer. His characters are fascinating, he sketches them easily, and quickly, gives a little back story to give them depth, and then moves on with the action. The action is what this book is all about. It starts with a bang, and keeps roaring along with only a few breaks to let readers recover their breath, and then on to the next plot twist. Iles definitely has a gift of keeping you on the edge of your seat--turning pages right up to the end. An altogether riveting read and my favorite so far of the 'Penn Cage' series. <br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11874914713969038678" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

